Code blocks work much like block quotes, only they begin and end with <code>&#96;&#96;&#96;</code> instead of `<<<`, and they display their contents in a fixed-width font, respecting line breaks. If you install the official Highlight [[plugin|Plugins]], you can also specify a language for [[syntax highlighting|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syntax_highlighting]] after the opening backticks.

